<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1438,383,1067]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,459,847,873]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<materialsCitation collectionCode="LC" county="Known" location="Pajapan" municipality="Santa Marta" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave">
Least Concern (
<collectionCode box="[682,722,848,874]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">LC</collectionCode>
) in 
<collectingRegion box="[775,883,848,874]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
. 
<collectingCounty box="[897,983,848,874]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Known</collectingCounty>
from five recent collections made in small natural forest fragments in central 
<collectingRegion box="[626,730,886,912]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
(not protected), and at the upper slopes of 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1234,1380,886,912]" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Santa Marta</collectingMunicipality>
, 
<collectingRegion country="Peru" name="San Martin" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">San Martín</collectingRegion>
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:184887DA8024FFEE90C8FEE41433B12D:953E60178024FFEE90B2FC4B1442B6B1" box="[237,330,925,951]" county="Known" municipality="Santa Marta" name="Pajapan" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" stateProvince="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave">Pajapan</location>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[385,515,925,951]" country="Peru" name="San Martin" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">San Martín</collectingRegion>
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:184887DA8024FFEE90C8FEE41433B12D:953E60178024FFEE9255FC4B175DB6B1" box="[522,597,925,951]" county="Known" municipality="Santa Marta" name="Tuxtla" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" stateProvince="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave">Tuxtla</location>
volcanoes, which are somewhat protected because they 
<taxonomicName box="[1254,1363,925,951]" form="part" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" rank="form">form part</taxonomicName>
of the nuclear zones of the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:184887DA8024FFEE90C8FEE41433B12D:953E60178024FFEE91D7FC1217F1B6D8" box="[392,761,964,990]" county="Known" municipality="Santa Marta" name="Los Tuxtlas Biosphere Reserve" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" stateProvince="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave">Los Tuxtlas Biosphere Reserve</location>
. However, their montane rain forest habitat in 
<collectingRegion box="[1305,1409,964,990]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="4" pageNumber="33">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
is still under high anthropogenic pressure, especially in the central region. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:184887DA8024FFEE90C8FEE41433B12D:953E60178024FFEE946AFC3C11B4B102" box="[1077,1212,1002,1028]" county="Known" municipality="Santa Marta" name="Specimens" pageId="4" pageNumber="33" stateProvince="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave">Specimens</location>
examined: 7; TK collections: 5
</materialsCitation>
.
